 $1+2+3+\cdots+100$ can be written as the sums $100+1$, $99+2$, $98+3$, $\cdots$, $51+50$. Because
\begin{align*}
100 + 1 & = 101, \\
99 + 2 & = 101, \\
98 + 3 & = 101, \text{and so on}
\end{align*}
there are $100/2=50$ sums each of which is $101$. So the answer is $50 \cdot 101 = 5050$.
